<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width">
    <meta name="keywords" content="Url, short, url shortener, qr, qrcode, generate, qrcode generator, generate qr, free, javascript, nodejs">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/public/favicon.svg">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/style.css">
    <title>Turu | Shorten url ðŸ”¥Generate QR</title>
</head>
<body>
<div id="home">
    <div id="landing">
        <main>
        <h1>Turu'ly easy, <br>Turu'ly FREE!!</h1>
        <section>
            <h2><u>Easy to use</u></h2>
            <p>Turu is an easy to use web app, to shorten any lengthy url and to generate a QR for any type of content such as a URL, text, JSON data,..</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2><u>Free for all, no login</u></h2>
            <p>The app is free to use without any requirement of login/signup.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2><u>Download QR</u></h2>
            <p>The QR generated can be downloaded directly.</p>
        </section>
        </main>
    </div>
    <div id="page">
        <div id="urlShortener">
            <form action="" method="post">
                <input type="text" name="url" class="url" placeholder="Shorten the url" required>
                <input type="submit" value="Shorten" class="btn">
            </form>
            <div id="shortened">
                <input type="text" name="shortenedurl" placeholder="Copy url" class="url" id="copy" value=<%= shorturl %>>
                <button onclick="myFunction()" class="btn">Copy</button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="generateqr">
            <form action="/getqr" method="get">
                <input type="text" name="qrurl" class="url" placeholder="URL to generate QR" required>
                <input type="submit" value="Generate QR" class="btn">
            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
<script>
    function myFunction() {
        var copyText = document.getElementById("copy");
        if(copyText.value) {
            copyText.select();
            copyText.setSelectionRange(0, 99999);  
            document.execCommand("copy");
            alert("Copied the URL: " + copyText.value);
        }
    }
</script>
</html>